      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pastry, chill",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub the {{unsalted-butter}} into the {{plain-flour}}, first {{caster-sugar}} and {{sea-salt-fine}}. Bind with the {{water}} a tablespoon at a time. Divide in two equal discs, wrap, chill an hour.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Filling and lattice",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 200°C fan. Mix the {{strawberries}}, {{rhubarb}}, second {{caster-sugar}}, {{cornflour}}, juice of the {{lemon}} and {{vanilla-extract}} in a bowl. Roll one pastry disc and line the pie dish. Tip the filling in. Roll the second disc to a rectangle 3 mm thick and cut into 1.5 cm wide strips with a ruler. ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "Weave a lattice top",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp99d8rp0000vsv4bzfk318l"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": "; seal the strip ends to the base rim.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, two stages",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Brush the lattice with the beaten {{eggs}} and scatter with {{demerara-sugar}}. Set on a tray. Bake at 200°C fan for 20 minutes, then drop to 180°C fan for another 30 to 35 minutes; the pastry should be deep gold and the filling should bubble visibly through the gaps. Cool an hour before slicing.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
